{
  "texts": [
    "• Gradient Boosting: Combines multiple weak learning models into a single robust model [34].",
    "The general idea is that the Gradient Boosting (GB) training process starts with a simple base model and fits it to the training data.",
    "Then, the residuals of this first base model are calculated.",
    "A new weak model is trained using the residuals as the target in each subsequent iteration.",
    "This new model is added to the existing ensemble of models and fitted to the updated residuals [30]."
  ]
}